    "LSTM is then used to model the sequential exercise results, and attention mechanism is used to assign different weights to features This work ignores the impact of the relation between knowledge concepts on student performance prediction Chen and Cui (2020) 2020 LMS (Canadian University) 668 students Learning Behavior/Activity features 5 features are selected from 21 LSTM AUC: 75.2% The study proposed an early prediction model that can examine student behavior/activity features The class imbalance for LSTM analysis (the test dataset is largely imbalanced), where training and test data needs to be come from the same feature and target distributions Xie (2021) 2021 MOOC (OULAD) 22 courses, 32,593 students, and 10,655,280 data Demographic, and Learning Behavior/Activity features -LSTM Four classes in Week25 Accuracy: 69.55% Precision: 62.95% Recall: 52.84% F1-Score: 51.50% Binary classes in Week25 Accuracy: 89.12% Precision: 92.07% Recall: 86.48% F1-Score: 89.18% The study added an attention layer into multi-layer LSTM model to predict student performance The number of features used were not mentioned in the paper The OULA dataset includes many feature that can help at improving the model accuracy Huang et al (2022) 2022 MOOC (OULAD) 22 online courses and 32,593 students Learning Behavior/Activity features 17 LSTM AUC: 84% The predictive model integrated dynamic features of learning behaviors for early detect of students who are at-risk of fail Experiments were only conducted on the data of one course Data used is not the raw log data, but the aggregated data on a daily basis which make it difficult to extract the sequence features of the learning behavior continued on the next page Brdesee et al (2022) 2022 LMS (Student Information System of a Saudi University) 230,000 students Demographic, Previous and Current Academic features 19 LSTM Accuracy: 85% AUC: 80% The proposed model predicted at-risk of fail students through assessing them on campus using demographic 